The Visual Query Editor displays information about the tables specified in 
the current frame definition.  

  * The frame name is displayed in the upper left corner of the screen.

  * The table type is shown at the top of the table information.

  * Lines drawn to the left of the tables indicate joins.  Multiple joins 
    are marked "a," "b," and so on.

  * The Display column lets you specify whether a field should be displayed 
    on the form, generate a local variable or hidden column, or neither.

  * Other fields (that vary according to type of frame) let you assign 
    specific or general characteristics to a form or restrict a query.
    (For detailed information, see Append, Browse, or Update frame 
    definition help.)

